Implements the heart of the SDK integration for the Java real-estate demo: the pipeline phase enum, the per-enquiry agent class with tool definitions, the application-scoped agent registry, and the CDI-managed `CopilotClient`.

## New files

- **`Phase.java`** — Six-value enum matching the C# pipeline: `QUEUED → VALIDATING → SEARCHING → WRITING_REPORT → DONE / REJECTED`

- **`CopilotClientProducer.java`** — `@Produces @ApplicationScoped` / `@Disposes` lifecycle for `CopilotClient` in `EMPTY` mode:
  ```java
  return new CopilotClient(new CopilotClientOptions()
      .setMode(CopilotClientMode.EMPTY)
      .setCopilotHome(Path.of(System.getProperty("user.home"), ".copilot").toString()));
  ```

- **`Agent.java`** — Showcases three tool-definition styles in one class:
  ```java
  // Style 1: @CopilotTool annotation (headline feature)
  @CopilotTool("Sets the current phase of the agent...")
  void setCurrentPhase(@CopilotToolParam("The phase to transition to") Phase phase) { ... }

  // Style 2: inline lambda + overridesBuiltInTool (ADR-006)
  ToolDefinition reportIntent = ToolDefinition
      .from("report_intent", "Reports the current intent...",
            Param.of(String.class, "intent", "Intent in max 4 words"),
            (String intent) -> { this.currentIntent = intent; notifyUi(); return "ok"; })
      .overridesBuiltInTool(true);

  // Style 3: @CopilotTool on PropertyDatabase (cross-class, see below)
  var dbTools = ToolDefinition.fromObject(db);
  ```
  Agent loop runs on a virtual thread via `Thread.ofVirtual().start(...)`. Session events collected for the detail view. `notifyUi()` is a placeholder wired in issue 3.4.

- **`AppState.java`** — `@ApplicationScoped` registry using `ConcurrentHashMap<String, Agent>`. `submitEnquiry()` creates an agent and dispatches it on a virtual thread; rejected agents are removed after a 15-second linger. `@PostConstruct` submits a smoke-test enquiry to confirm wiring at startup.

## Modified files

- **`PropertyDatabase.java`** — Added `@CopilotTool searchProperties(...)` with full `@CopilotToolParam` annotations on all six parameters, delegating to the existing `search()` method.

- **`pom.xml`** — Added GitHub Packages `<repository>` entry for `copilot-sdk-java` so CI can resolve the SNAPSHOT dependency.

